Usage: write_text_timing_report [-help] [-category <string>] [-format <string>]
                                [-mtarpt <string>]
                                [-path_specification <string>] -report <string>
                                [-summary]

-help                            # Prints out the command usage
-category <string>               # Specifies the category of paths to write to
                                 # the text file (string, optional)
-format <string>                 # Formats the report according to the
                                 # specified column name and its width.
                                 # Multiple column names can be specified.
                                 # {{column1 width1} {column2 width2} ...}
                                 # (string, optional)
-mtarpt <string>                 # Specifies the name of the .mtarpt file to
                                 # read and convert to a text file.
                                 # (string, optional)
-path_specification <string>     # Writes a single number or path range
                                 # separated by blank space. A path range is
                                 # two numbers separated by a minus - sign
                                 # (string, optional)
-report <string>                 # Specifies the name of the text output file
                                 # (string, required)
-summary                         # Formats the report according to the
                                 # specified column name and its width.
                                 # Multiple column names can be specified.
                                 # (bool, optional)